      "author_association": "MEMBER",
      "body": "I very much like the idea of the wrapper approach described in https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/30983#issuecomment-237920497, it feels to me like the correct way to structure and package an application consisting of multiple binaries rather than overloading existing binaries with even more options.\r\n\r\nMy only reservation with the approach is the potential magnitude of the effects downstream. If executed poorly this could break many scripts, programs and general infra. However, so long as we maintain the current binary names in the current directory, as currently proposed, and only introduce a new wrapper around them, then it seems like it should mitigate any downstream impact (completely).",
